// Flink exactly-once checkpoint validation
@Test
public void testExactlyOnceProcessing() {
  StreamExecutionEnvironment env = StreamExecutionEnvironment
    .getTestEnvironment();
  env.enableCheckpointing(1000);
  env.getCheckpointConfig().setCheckpointingMode(
    CheckpointingMode.EXACTLY_ONCE);

  // Test data consistency across checkpoints
  TestDataStream<String> source = env.fromElements(testEvents);
  DataStream<Result> processed = source
    .keyBy(event -> event.getUserId())
    .window(TumblingProcessingTimeWindows.of(Time.seconds(5)))
    .process(new ExactlyOnceWindowFunction());

  // Validate state consistency after restarts
  assertExactlyOnceResults(processed);
}
```

## Implementation Details

The testing framework leverages container orchestration for namespace isolation, enabling parallel test execution without interference. Synthetic data generators use cryptographic seeds to ensure reproducible event streams across test runs, while failure injection simulates realistic production scenarios including network partitions, broker outages, and Redis connection failures. Metrics collection validates latency thresholds, throughput guarantees, and error rates against SLA requirements.

