- **Per-node isolation vs. cross-node consistency**: Each node maintains its own cache; invalidation must propagate to all nodes
- **Cache stampede and coalescing**: Prevents thundering herd when cache misses occur simultaneously
- **Time manipulation in CI**: Essential for testing TTL behavior without waiting in tests
